  <notes>
    This task is mandatory per CLAUDE.md §7 and task-create Step 3.7 — do not skip even if "the work feels done."

    Key R4 lesson to capture in lessons-learned.md: the project's core thesis was "JPS is data, not code. Source-code changes are necessary but not sufficient — corresponding sprk_analysisaction + sprk_analysisplaybook rows must be deployed to each environment." If a future project ships a new NodeExecutor, ActionType enum value, or playbook, the developer MUST deploy the corresponding Dataverse rows or the feature is silently inert. R4 added §10-style hygiene awareness for this concern; consider promoting it into a §10 sub-bullet for future projects.

    If R3 PR #451 is still open at wrap-up time, document the coordination handoff (which PR merged first, which conflicts surfaced, how they were resolved) so the team has a precedent.
  </notes>

